<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>Does Quora help with SEO?</strong></p>
<p>Yes. Quora helps SEO in 3 ways: referral traffic from answers that link to your site, SERP visibility when Quora pages rank for your target keywords, and brand authority signals that strengthen your <a href="/blog/eeat-google-quality-guide/">E-E-A-T profile</a>. The links are nofollow, so they do not directly pass PageRank. But the indirect SEO benefits are significant.</p>
<p><strong>Are Quora backlinks dofollow or nofollow?</strong></p>
<p>All links on Quora carry a <code>rel="nofollow"</code> attribute. Google does not count them as direct ranking signals. However, nofollow links still drive referral traffic, help Google discover new pages, and create brand mentions that contribute to entity authority.</p>
<p><strong>How many Quora answers should I write per week?</strong></p>
<p>Aim for 5 to 7 answers per week (1 per business day). Consistency matters more than volume. Focus on quality answers in your niche rather than spreading across unrelated topics. At this pace, you will have 260+ indexed answers within a year.</p>
<p><strong>Can Quora answers rank on Google?</strong></p>
<p>Yes. Quora has a domain authority of 93. Many Quora pages rank on page 1 for long-tail queries. Google's recent algorithm updates have increased the visibility of forum and discussion content in search results. Your answer on a ranking Quora page gets organic traffic from Google without any work on your own site.</p>
<p><strong>Is Quora better than Reddit for SEO?</strong></p>
<p>Both platforms offer SEO value, but they serve different purposes. Quora is better for long-form expert answers and <a href="/blog/what-is-topical-authority/">building topical authority</a>. Reddit is better for community engagement and trending discussions. For SEO specifically, Quora has a higher domain authority and more structured content that Google ranks consistently.</p>
<p><strong>How do I avoid getting banned on Quora?</strong></p>
<p>Follow 3 rules: never include more than 1 link per answer, never paste the same answer across multiple questions, and always provide genuine value before mentioning your brand. Quora's moderation team flags accounts that post promotional content without adding substance. Focus on being helpful first. The marketing results follow.</p>
